      <p class="eyebrow">Emergency plumbing</p>
      <h2>When a Brampton plumbing problem needs urgent help</h2>
      <p>Some plumbing problems can be scheduled. Others need fast action because water damage gets expensive quickly. Call immediately if you have a burst pipe, sewage backing up into the basement, water near electrical equipment, a toilet that will not stop overflowing, a water heater leaking from the tank, or a fixture that cannot be isolated with a shutoff valve.</p>
      <p>If it is safe, shut off the nearest valve or the main water supply before calling. Take a quick photo or video of the issue if you can do it safely. That helps explain the situation clearly and lets the technician prepare for the type of repair: leak repair, pipe replacement, drain clearing, sewer inspection, water heater isolation, or fixture shutoff work.</p>
    </div>
    <aside class="quick-card urgent-card">
      <h2>Emergency signs</h2>
