      <p class="eyebrow">Plumber in Brampton FAQ</p>
      <h2>Common questions before calling a Brampton plumber</h2>
    </div>
    <details><summary>Do you provide same-day plumbing service in Brampton?</summary><p>Same-day service depends on schedule and urgency. Active leaks, sewer backups, burst pipes, and major fixture failures are treated as priority calls. For non-emergency work, call or request service and we will help choose the next available appointment.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Do you offer 24/7 emergency plumbing in Brampton?</summary><p>Yes. Call 647-980-9211 for urgent plumbing problems such as burst pipes, sewer backups, overflowing toilets, active leaks, and emergency shutoff support.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What plumbing services do you provide?</summary><p>Fateh helps with emergency plumbing, drain cleaning, clogged toilets, leak detection, pipe repair, sewer line repair, water heater repair, toilet repair, faucet repair, sump pump repair, kitchen plumbing, and commercial plumbing calls.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Can you fix clogged drains and clogged toilets?</summary><p>Yes. We help with clogged sinks, blocked toilets, slow tubs, kitchen drains, floor drains, recurring clogs, and main drain concerns. If the issue keeps returning, a camera inspection or sewer line service may be recommended.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Do you repair water heaters in Brampton?</summary><p>Yes. We help with no hot water, leaking tanks, inconsistent temperature, pilot or ignition issues, replacement planning, and plumbing connections around the water heater.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Should I shut off the water before calling?</summary><p>If water is actively leaking, shut off the nearest fixture valve or the main water shutoff if it is safe to do so. If water is near electrical equipment, avoid touching the area and call for help right away.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Which Brampton neighbourhoods do you serve?</summary><p>Fateh serves Brampton areas including Bramalea, Springdale, Castlemore, Mount Pleasant, Heart Lake, Fletcher's Meadow, Credit Valley, Peel Village, Downtown Brampton, and nearby communities.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Do you handle residential and commercial plumbing?</summary><p>Yes. Fateh helps homeowners, landlords, restaurants, retail units, property managers, and small businesses with plumbing repairs, emergency calls, maintenance issues, and service planning.</p></details>
